## Enterprise Compliance Rollup
Tenants monitored: {{enterprise_rollup.tenant_count}}
Average Compliance Score: {{enterprise_rollup.avg_compliance_pct}}%
Range: {{enterprise_rollup.min_compliance_pct}}% – {{enterprise_rollup.max_compliance_pct}}%
Tenant needing most attention: {{enterprise_rollup.lowest_tenant}}

## Per-Tenant Compliance Scores
{% for t in tenant_summaries %}
- {{t.display_name}} ({{t.department or 'N/A'}}): {{t.compliance_pct}}% ({{t.current_score}}/{{t.max_score}} pts) as of {{t.snapshot_date}}
{% endfor %}

## Week-over-Week Compliance Trends
{% for w in weekly_changes %}
- {{w.display_name}} ({{w.department or 'N/A'}}): {{w.current_pct}}% ({{w.trend_direction}}, {{w.wow_change}}% change)
{% endfor %}

{% if department_rollup %}
## Department / Agency Rollup
{% for d in department_rollup %}
- {{d.department}}: {{d.avg_compliance_pct}}% avg across {{d.tenant_count}} tenant(s) — {{d.total_assessments}} assessment(s), {{d.total_failed_controls}} failed controls
{% endfor %}
{% endif %}

## Top Assessment Control Gaps
{% for g in top_gaps %}
- {{g.control_name}} [{{g.control_family}}, {{g.regulation or 'N/A'}}]: affects {{g.affected_tenants}} tenant(s), avg gap {{g.avg_gap | round(1)}} pts — {{g.implementation_status}}
{% endfor %}

Generate a weekly Compliance Manager digest with:
1. A 2-sentence executive summary (lead with the Compliance Score number)
2. Which tenants improved or declined this week, with percentage changes
3. Department/agency performance comparison (if data available)
4. Assessment coverage — which regulations are well-covered vs. at risk
5. The top 3 recommended actions to take this week (with business justification)
6. A closing sentence on overall compliance posture trend direction

Keep the total length under 450 words. Use plain language — no technical jargon.
This report will be shared with organizational leadership.
